<paragraph id="8BF636F36920FF8DDFA8FB05FD41E796" blockId="19.[151,664,1224,1251]" box="[151,664,1224,1251]" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">
<heading id="D0BE819F6920FF8DDFA8FB05FD41E796" bold="true" box="[151,664,1224,1251]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDFA8FB05FD41E796" bold="true" box="[151,664,1224,1251]" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">
Comparison of 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDE67FB04FE09E796" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[344,464,1224,1250]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laticeps">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDE67FB04FE09E796" bold="true" box="[344,464,1224,1250]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">P. laticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDD31FB04FD41E796" baseAuthorityName="Dumeril &amp; Bibron" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[526,664,1224,1250]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burchelli">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDD31FB04FD41E796" bold="true" box="[526,664,1224,1250]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">P. burchelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35365786920FF8DDFA8FAC3FE06E58B" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF636F36920FF8DDFA8FAC3FD37E552" blockId="19.[151,1437,1295,1791]" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">
The most informative characters to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDD86FADCFCF6E65C" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[697,815,1295,1320]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laticeps">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDD86FADCFCF6E65C" box="[697,815,1295,1320]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">P. laticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDC46FADCFC25E65C" baseAuthorityName="Dumeril &amp; Bibron" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[889,1020,1295,1320]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burchelli">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDC46FADCFC25E65C" box="[889,1020,1295,1320]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">P. burchelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found to be (in combination): having 46 to 64 dorsal scale rows (
<quantity id="4CB19B166920FF8DDD0FFAFFFD6AE638" box="[560,691,1331,1356]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8288" metricValueMax="2.032" metricValueMin="1.6256" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" unit="in" value="72.0" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="64.0">64 to 80 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDD83FAFFFCF9E638" baseAuthorityName="Dumeril &amp; Bibron" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[700,800,1331,1356]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burchelli">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDD83FAFFFCF9E638" box="[700,800,1331,1356]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">burchelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 16 to 18 enlarged longitudinal ventral scale rows across the midbody at the median transverse ventral row (
<quantity id="4CB19B166920FF8DDC20FA94FC43E604" box="[799,922,1367,1392]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" metricValueMax="4.064" metricValueMin="3.048" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" unit="in" value="14.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="12.0">12 to 16 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDC9FFA9BFBDDE604" baseAuthorityName="Dumeril &amp; Bibron" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[928,1028,1367,1392]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burchelli">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDC9FFA9BFBDDE604" box="[928,1028,1367,1392]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">burchelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDB9BFA94FACEE604" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[1188,1303,1367,1392]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laticeps">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDB9BFA94FACEE604" box="[1188,1303,1367,1392]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">P. laticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
usually has 3 bulging nasal scales on each side with the interior ones separated from each other (non-bulging or only slightly bulging and broadly in contact in 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDD16FA53FD54E6CC" baseAuthorityName="Dumeril &amp; Bibron" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[553,653,1439,1464]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burchelli">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDD16FA53FD54E6CC" box="[553,653,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">burchelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), five or more upper labials anterior to the subocular (mostly 
<quantity id="4CB19B166920FF8DDA52FA6CFA45E6CC" box="[1389,1436,1439,1464]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDFA8FA0AFF22E6AB" baseAuthorityName="Dumeril &amp; Bibron" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[151,251,1478,1503]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burchelli">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDFA8FA0AFF22E6AB" box="[151,251,1478,1503]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">burchelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), five or more pairs of chin shields (mostly 
<quantity id="4CB19B166920FF8DDDCCFA0BFCC6E6AB" box="[755,799,1478,1503]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDC18FA0AFC52E6AB" baseAuthorityName="Dumeril &amp; Bibron" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[807,907,1478,1503]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burchelli">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDC18FA0AFC52E6AB" box="[807,907,1478,1503]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">burchelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 28–32 lamellae beneath the 4th toe (
<quantity id="4CB19B166920FF8DDA09FA0AFA45E6AB" box="[1334,1436,1478,1503]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.731" metricValueMax="7.112" metricValueMin="6.35" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" unit="in" value="26.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="25.0">25–28 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDFA8FA26FF22E577" baseAuthorityName="Dumeril &amp; Bibron" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[151,251,1514,1539]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burchelli">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDFA8FA26FF22E577" box="[151,251,1514,1539]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">burchelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and generally more and smaller granules around the supraoculars; particularly the inner row of granules around the supraoculars is always absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDDBCF9C2FD3EE553" baseAuthorityName="Dumeril &amp; Bibron" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[643,743,1550,1575]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burchelli">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDDBCF9C2FD3EE553" box="[643,743,1550,1575]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">burchelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF636F36920FF8DDFF8F9FEFE06E58B" blockId="19.[151,1437,1295,1791]" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">
Based on the re-description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDD17F9FFFD45E53F" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[552,668,1586,1611]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laticeps">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDD17F9FFFD45E53F" box="[552,668,1586,1611]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">P. laticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDDE9F9FFFC81E53F" baseAuthorityName="Dumeril &amp; Bibron" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[726,856,1586,1611]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burchelli">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDDE9F9FFFC81E53F" box="[726,856,1586,1611]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">P. burchelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
we conclude that BMNH 1988.512 collected as 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDAB8F9FFFF37E51B" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1845" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laticeps">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDAB8F9FFFF37E51B" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">P. laticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in fact 
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDE64F99BFE38E51B" box="[347,481,1622,1647]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDE64F99BFE04E51B" baseAuthorityName="Dumeril &amp; Bibron" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[347,477,1622,1647]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Pedioplanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="burchelli">P. burchelli</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
as it has only 14 transverse ventral scale rows, 72 dorsal scale rows, only 10 granules in front of the supraoculars, only 4 chin shields. Additionally, specimen BMNH 1988.515 can be identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D706920FF8DDFA8F952FEE7E5C3" baseAuthorityName="Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[151,318,1694,1719]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Meroles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="knoxii">
<emphasis id="B93DEAE16920FF8DDFA8F952FEE7E5C3" box="[151,318,1694,1719]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="101">Meroles knoxii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the subocular is separated from the lip by a labial scale, it has 3 scales rather than several small granules anterior to the first supraocular, and 4 chin shields of which only the first two are in contact along their entire interior edge (
<tableCitation id="C6CB03486920FF8DDE45F92AFE0BE58B" box="[378,466,1766,1791]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="10.[125,207,457,478]" captionTargetBox="[125,1852,624,1690]" captionTargetId="graphics@10.[111,1878,617,1691]" captionText="TABLE 2. Inđiviđuals presenteđ to us as Pedioplanis laticeps anđ their character values. The catalogue number of the type material is unđerlineđ. Values for symmetric characters are given as left / right unless they are the same on both siđes. Interstitial extra scales are remarkeđ as + 1. Abbreviations: ađ: ađult; subađ: subađult; juv: juvenile; hatch: hatchling; m: male; f: female; NA: not available; Ns: nasal scale; b: bulging; sb: slightly bulging; nb: not bulging; TVR: transverse ventral scale row; LVR: longituđinal ventral scale rows; max: maximum; LDR: longituđinal đorsal scale rows; PF: prefrontal; FN: frontonasal; F: frontal; TyS: tympanic shielđ; UL: upper labial; SbO: subocular scale; FreO: freno-ocular; LL: lower labial; FPo: femoral pores; C: enlargeđ collar scales; O: occipital; IP: interparietal; SO: supraocular; IRG: inner row of granules; inc.: incomplete; CS: chin shielđ pairs; FreN: freno-nasal; SC: supraciliaries. * Collecteđ by Smith. ** Presenteđ by Lorđ Derby. *** Ađđitional scale / granule between IP anđ O." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF36667B6939FF94DF42FE05F9B3E128" pageId="19" pageNumber="101" tableUuid="DF36667B6939FF94DF42FE05F9B3E128">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
